{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a07ba961a1c496e0b","tool_use_id":"toolu_012MZbfjHePicGzYWC4nnMb1","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore workflow view code","usage":{"total_tokens":50526,"tool_uses":9,"duration_ms":18808},"uuid":"cee21466-8b5f-4b97-ae6b-c4ad067e2e07","session_id":"b7dbfca6-10f0-424a-ad17-d251cbedaa77"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012MZbfjHePicGzYWC4nnMb1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I've found the bug. Let me document my findings:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've successfully identified the **project page workflow view** UI component and pinpointed the exact bug where clicking on a step shows a filename but doesn't load the file contents.\n\n### Bug Location\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` and `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\n### The Bug\n\nIn the **Step Drawer component** (lines 251-284 of project_detail.html), when a user clicks on a workflow step node in the DAG visualization:\n\n1. **The `openDrawer()` function** (line 251) displays the step metadata (name, type, results, config keys like \"prompt\", \"command\", \"script\") showing the **filename** in lines 263-264:\n```javascript\nbody += '<dt>' + k + '</dt><dd class=\"mono\">' + step.config[k] + '</dd>';\n```\n\n2. **The content fetch** (line 274) attempts to load the actual file contents:\n```javascript\nfetch('/api/projects/' + encodeURIComponent(projectLabel) + '/workflows/' + \n    encodeURIComponent(workflowName) + '/steps/' + encodeURIComponent(stepName) + '/content')\n```\n\n### The Root Cause\n\nThe backend handler **`handleAPIStepContent()`** in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1134-1199) has a **logic flaw** when trying to load file content:\n\n1. **For \"prompt\" files** (lines 1177-1182): It tries to read from `filepath.Join(dir, prompt)` where `prompt` is the config value. This should work if the path is correct.\n\n2. **For \"command\" fields** (lines 1184-1186): It returns the command string directly (not a file read) - this works fine.\n\n3. **For \"script\" fields** (lines 1188-1195): It tries to read as a file first with `os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, script))`, and if that fails, it falls back to returning the script string directly.\n\n4. **The problem**: If the path resolution fails at all steps, it returns a 404 \"no content available\" (line 1198).\n\n### Key Code Sections\n\n**Frontend (project_detail.html, lines 251-284):**\n- Displays step name in drawer header\n- Shows metadata including the config fields (which contain filenames)\n- Fetches content from `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n- The content placeholder is shown while loading, then replaced with the fetched content\n\n**Backend (handler.go, lines 1134-1199 - `handleAPIStepContent()`):**\n- Resolves the project directory\n- Finds the workflow definition\n- Locates the step in the workflow\n- Attempts to read referenced files based on step config\n- Returns plain text response with the file contents\n\n**UI Components:**\n- **Drawer component** (HTML lines 40-47): A fixed slide-out panel on the right side with header and scrollable body\n- **CSS styling** (style.css lines 491-548): Defines the drawer's appearance and animation\n\n### Related Files\n\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - The main template with the workflow DAG and step drawer UI\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Contains all HTTP handlers including `handleAPIStepContent()`\n3. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - CSS for the drawer and related components\n4. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Base layout template\n5. `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Domain model for workflows (referenced by dsl.Parse)\n\nThe workflow visualization is an SVG DAG (lines 163-249 of project_detail.html) with clickable step nodes that trigger `openDrawer()` function, which then attempts to fetch and display step content via a REST API endpoint."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a07ba961a1c496e0b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 51462\ntool_uses: 9\nduration_ms: 18813</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b7dbfca6-10f0-424a-ad17-d251cbedaa77","uuid":"80c6c0ff-959e-4dbb-9b7d-2d64abfecf21","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to find the code related to the \"project page workflow view\" where clicking on a step shows a filename but doesn't load the file contents. This is likely a web UI or TUI component. Search thoroughly for:\n\n1. Any web/UI/TUI code related to workflow visualization or step display\n2. Files related to \"project page\" or \"workflow view\"\n3. Any template files, HTML, or terminal UI code\n4. Handlers or API endpoints that serve step/prompt content\n5. Look for patterns like \"prompt\", \"script\", \"step\" in UI-related files\n\nSearch across the entire codebase. Be very thorough - check cmd/, internal/, web/, ui/, static/, templates/, and any other directories.","agentId":"a07ba961a1c496e0b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I've found the bug. Let me document my findings:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've successfully identified the **project page workflow view** UI component and pinpointed the exact bug where clicking on a step shows a filename but doesn't load the file contents.\n\n### Bug Location\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` and `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\n### The Bug\n\nIn the **Step Drawer component** (lines 251-284 of project_detail.html), when a user clicks on a workflow step node in the DAG visualization:\n\n1. **The `openDrawer()` function** (line 251) displays the step metadata (name, type, results, config keys like \"prompt\", \"command\", \"script\") showing the **filename** in lines 263-264:\n```javascript\nbody += '<dt>' + k + '</dt><dd class=\"mono\">' + step.config[k] + '</dd>';\n```\n\n2. **The content fetch** (line 274) attempts to load the actual file contents:\n```javascript\nfetch('/api/projects/' + encodeURIComponent(projectLabel) + '/workflows/' + \n    encodeURIComponent(workflowName) + '/steps/' + encodeURIComponent(stepName) + '/content')\n```\n\n### The Root Cause\n\nThe backend handler **`handleAPIStepContent()`** in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1134-1199) has a **logic flaw** when trying to load file content:\n\n1. **For \"prompt\" files** (lines 1177-1182): It tries to read from `filepath.Join(dir, prompt)` where `prompt` is the config value. This should work if the path is correct.\n\n2. **For \"command\" fields** (lines 1184-1186): It returns the command string directly (not a file read) - this works fine.\n\n3. **For \"script\" fields** (lines 1188-1195): It tries to read as a file first with `os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, script))`, and if that fails, it falls back to returning the script string directly.\n\n4. **The problem**: If the path resolution fails at all steps, it returns a 404 \"no content available\" (line 1198).\n\n### Key Code Sections\n\n**Frontend (project_detail.html, lines 251-284):**\n- Displays step name in drawer header\n- Shows metadata including the config fields (which contain filenames)\n- Fetches content from `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n- The content placeholder is shown while loading, then replaced with the fetched content\n\n**Backend (handler.go, lines 1134-1199 - `handleAPIStepContent()`):**\n- Resolves the project directory\n- Finds the workflow definition\n- Locates the step in the workflow\n- Attempts to read referenced files based on step config\n- Returns plain text response with the file contents\n\n**UI Components:**\n- **Drawer component** (HTML lines 40-47): A fixed slide-out panel on the right side with header and scrollable body\n- **CSS styling** (style.css lines 491-548): Defines the drawer's appearance and animation\n\n### Related Files\n\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - The main template with the workflow DAG and step drawer UI\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Contains all HTTP handlers including `handleAPIStepContent()`\n3. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - CSS for the drawer and related components\n4. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Base layout template\n5. `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Domain model for workflows (referenced by dsl.Parse)\n\nThe workflow visualization is an SVG DAG (lines 163-249 of project_detail.html) with clickable step nodes that trigger `openDrawer()` function, which then attempts to fetch and display step content via a REST API endpoint."}],"totalDurationMs":18813,"totalTokens":51462,"totalToolUseCount":9,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9583,"cache_read_input_tokens":40910,"output_tokens":965,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":9583},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
