{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01MMbyeTqDAFPeqPnFHnhp9u","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Clean build. Here's a summary of the fix:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### Root Cause\nThe DSL parser stores prompt/script values with `file(\"...\")` wrapper syntax (e.g. `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")`), but the `handleAPIStepContent` handler was using this raw value directly as a file path, causing the file read to fail.\n\nAdditionally, the handler checked `step.Config[\"command\"]` but the DSL uses `\"run\"` as the key.\n\n### Files Changed\n\n1. **`internal/adapters/web/handler.go`**:\n   - Added `extractFilePath()` helper that unwraps `file(\"path\")` → `path`\n   - Fixed prompt file reading to use `extractFilePath(prompt)` before building the file path\n   - Changed `step.Config[\"command\"]` → `step.Config[\"run\"]` to match the DSL key\n   - Applied same `extractFilePath()` to the script path handling\n\n2. **`internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`**:\n   - Added `\"run\"` to the displayed config keys in the step drawer (alongside existing `\"command\"`)\n\n3. **`internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go`**:\n   - Added `TestExtractFilePath` - unit tests for the path unwrapping helper\n   - Added `TestAPIStepContent_PromptFile` - integration test verifying prompt file content is loaded\n   - Added `TestAPIStepContent_RunCommand` - integration test verifying run commands are returned\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":263,"cache_read_input_tokens":49818,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":263},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b7dbfca6-10f0-424a-ad17-d251cbedaa77","uuid":"a62cba22-54a5-432d-b19d-bc22ad2f6995"}
